@startuml uc-05-statediagram
title UC05 — Student learns vocabulary by selected level/topic — State Diagram
skinparam state {
  BackgroundColor #FEFEFE
  BorderColor #333333
  FontName Helvetica
}

[*] --> WaitingForAccess

WaitingForAccess --> LevelRequired : user has no selected level
LevelRequired --> WaitingForTopic : level A1-C2 selected
WaitingForAccess --> WaitingForTopic : authenticated + selected level exists

WaitingForTopic --> LoadingVocabulary : choose topic in selected level
LoadingVocabulary --> DisplayingActiveContent : active crawled/Admin-managed words found
LoadingVocabulary --> DisplayingCachedContent : latest crawl failed\ncache available
LoadingVocabulary --> EmptyContent : no active/cache content

DisplayingActiveContent --> StudyingWord : open word/flashcard
DisplayingCachedContent --> StudyingWord : continue with cached words
StudyingWord --> ProgressSaving : mark learned / update progress
ProgressSaving --> ProgressSaved : save user_word_progress\nand user_topic_progress
ProgressSaved --> DisplayingActiveContent : continue topic

DisplayingActiveContent --> ContentRefreshed : weekly crawl auto-published\nnew active vocabulary
ContentRefreshed --> DisplayingActiveContent : refresh list, keep history

DisplayingActiveContent --> ContentDisabled : Admin disables crawled content
DisplayingCachedContent --> ContentDisabled : Admin disables cached item
ContentDisabled --> LoadingVocabulary : reload active words only

LoadingVocabulary --> Error : access/API/data error
ProgressSaving --> Error : save failed
Error --> LoadingVocabulary : retry request
Error --> WaitingForTopic : choose another topic

EmptyContent --> WaitingForTopic : choose another topic
ProgressSaved --> [*]

note right of DisplayingCachedContent
  Cache fallback is used when
  Langeek crawl fails or is unavailable.
end note

note right of ContentRefreshed
  Source: weekly Langeek crawler.
  Published content is active immediately,
  unless Admin later edits/disables it.
end note
@enduml
